opicID=14.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> What are the epic quests about?</span><hr size=1> As we all know, there is one epic quest for each class.<br>
<br>
But what are theese quests about, really? <br>
And what are their rewards?<br>
With what I don't mean stats, effect and look, but nature.<br>
<br>
From a roleplaying perspective, I'm sure that King Artur and his Knights didn't seek the holy grail merely for it's statbonuses and clickable effect <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
The only quest I know a bit about is the mage quest. Vould people who know about the others fill in a bit please?<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uedeina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Edeina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Board Mistress</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/15/01 11:38:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The mage Quest</span><hr size=1> The magician epic quest is a quest for knowledge and power: a academic research project with a violent twist.<br>
<br>
A long time ago a mage named Magi'knot found out about the ultimate summoning: the orb of mastery that manifests complete mastery over all four elements. Magi'knot sought this knowledge, but failed and died a horrible death.<br>
<br>
Now the character follow in magi'knots footsteps, determined to succeed where he failed. After some research (minor starting quests) she realize that the knowledge of the orb of mastery can be obtained from the one called the master of the elements. However, to achieve this, she need the four elements in their purest form, something that only the four element masters can produce. Thus, she must seek out these four masters and convince them to give her their respective element. Of course, they will put her through tests and demand huge favors. It is also said that these subquests are necessary training: a mage that possess the orb of mastery but don't have the skill and power to control it will perish just like Magi'knot. <br>
<br>
The final reward is the knowledge of the ultimate magician spell. This summoning consists of a staff and a elemental pet. Both the weapon and the pet are far superior then anything else the mage can produce. This superiority lies not only in their power (great stats), but also in their nature (staff don't poof when linkdead, pet don't require a reagent).<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/bayonaero.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=qwik>Qwik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/15/01 9:17:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The mage Quest</span><hr size=1> ok now this is what i dont understand bout the mage quest ok ..... now i read bout it on the old CT msg board and someoen sadi something bout destroying it and gettin a new one? or i dont konw but is there unlimited charges for the pet? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uedeina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Edeina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Board Mistress</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/15/01 9:57:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The mage Quest</span><hr size=1> Simple: our epic is not a item, it is a spell. <br>
With this spell you can summon a unlimited number of epic staffs.<br>
Sadly they are nodrop and lore, so you have to destroy the old (or duel) to get a new.<br>
Each staff has one charce of summon uberpet. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ukivornteleri.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kivorn Teleri</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Gimpy Ranger Admin</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/16/01 3:20:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/alex_enstrom/kiv60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The mage Quest</span><hr size=1> Which means, in short, don't mess with a mage with an epic... she'll have one über pet summoned and just one click away from another one.<br>
<br>
The ranger quest is pretty cool.<br>
It all starts out as you sense "an evil" stalking the lands.<br>
At first you start out by identifying this evil.<br>
It turns out to be innoruuk, and thus we must kick his goon's, Venril Sathir's, ass.<br>
Then we're to reforge a blade given to us.<br>
In the process to do so we have to find one of the hammers used to construct old paineel, a hammer with the soul of a dwarven smith in it. Once we free the little bugger (we let the dorf out! ah-ruff!) he smiths us a sword that we hand in to the quest NPC to recieve our off-hand sword, Swiftwind.<br>
Then we get to wax Innoruuk's tail (strike directly against the evil) and hand in a drop off his corpse to a treant in the Karanas for our mainhand sword.<br>
<br>
All in all, a cool quest.<br>
