Long ago I heard a warrior saying his quest was just a shoppinglist. Seems he was right <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujableakl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jableakl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/28/01 7:19:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: warrior epic</span><hr size=1> From a roleplaying perspective the bard epic is about creating the ultimate symphony. The balance between ballad and battle. The ultimate untensil for creating your story as well as helping you sing it. To this end a bard must finish a task of epic proportions for which they can put to poetry and prose.<br>
<br>
