<br>
<br>
the original point of this thread was about the nature of the storyline behind the quests...<br>
<br>
the Cleric epic is about the forces of the water triumverate (tarew marr etc...) overcoming the fiery god Solusek Ro,<br>
<br>
it starts with a plasmatic priest (cronies of Sol Ro) in lake rathe trying to upset the balance between fire goblins and aqua goblins.. and you unwittingly do his bidding by killing the king of the water goblins, that is when the priest shows his true intentions, to DESTROY THE WORLD AHAHAHAH (yeah cliche, i know)<br>
<br>
from there you must run around the world thwarting Solusek Ro's minions and eventually discover a secret pact between the Sarnak collective and the priests of Sol Ro to summon forth a fire spirit who will consume the world in its flames (thats ixiblat)<br>
<br>
the final battle (campfest) is the leader of the plasmatic priests himself, an exiled elder dragon named Zordicalickus Ragefire! disguised as a lowly human vendor, he has taken over the fortified remains of Lord Nagafens dungeon; claiming it as his base of operations. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ulummusl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LummusL</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/18/01 11:38:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What are the epic quests about?</span><hr size=1> The REAL story of the warrior epic is lost glory renewed. Redblade, the smith in Freeport is very much content toiling away countless hours at the forge along with his Dwaven friend in spite of his ancestry of being of a linage of great warriors faithful to Rallos Zek. He wears the Red Scabbard as a token to his lineage, but it will be neither himself or his jealous, spiteful brother that will ever know the scabbards true meaning and power. It will be that brave warrior that dares to dig deeper into what the scabbard means....<br>
    Half of the quest is rediscovery of the lost pieces of Redblade's ancestral weapon, The Jagged Blade of War. Dispersed across Norrath after his Great, great, great etc etc Grandfather's fall to the enemies of Rallos Zek, it is the task of the warrior to find these relics. Many are just lost under the sands and earth of time, such as the hilts and the first blade while others are held by less than savory creatures, such as the Chardok Queen.<br>
    The second part is the restoration of the powers of the Scabbard in order to bind the scattered relics into one weapon of power. This mainly is done by avenging Redblade's ancestor by slaying the enemies of Rallos Zek and taking an imbued trouphy from each one of the slain foes. This also stands as a testament of the power of the warrior as it proves you are worthy, in addition to avenging Redblade. He will hand you the Red Scabbard along with instructions on how to summon forth either the Jagged Blade of War or the Blade of Tactics and the Blade of Strategy from the relics you have collected and restored.<br>
<br>
Kind of an abridged, Cliff Notes version.<br>
